# Structuring tabular data

### When to use tables

- Tabular data
- Information that is best conveyed in a table

### Building table rows

```html
<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Company</th>
    <th>Contact</th>
    <th>Country</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Alfreds Futterkiste</td>
    <td>Maria Anders</td>
    <td>Germany</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Centro comercial Moctezuma</td>
    <td>Francisco Chang</td>
    <td>Mexico</td>
  </tr>
</table>
```
- ```<table>``` wraps around the whole table
- ```<tr>``` wraps around a set of elements, defining them as beloning to the same row. Attributes:
  - ```colspan```
  - ```rowspan```
  - ```headers```
- ```<th>``` defines a header for a column. Attributes:
  - ```colspan```
  - ```rowspan```
  - ```scope```
- ```<td>``` marks the actual bits of data
- Content of the header in the first row.